   "source": [
    "# Bank Customer Churn Prediction\n",
    "**Author:** Alfred Shingai  \n"
    "**Tools:** Python · Pandas · Scikit-learn · Matplotlib · Seaborn\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Project Overview\n",
    "This project builds an end-to-end machine learning pipeline to predict which bank customers are likely to churn (close their account). It covers:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Data Cleaning & Merging** — fixing messy real-world data across two Excel sheets  \n",
    "2. **Exploratory Data Analysis** — uncovering churn patterns through visualisations  \n",
    "3. **Feature Engineering** — creating new signals to improve model performance  \n",
    "4. **ML Modelling** — training and comparing three classifiers with proper evaluation  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset:** 10,000 customers · 2 sheets · 1 target variable (`Exited`)  \n",
    "**Best Model:** Gradient Boosting · AUC-ROC = 0.868"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ad1d85d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0 · Imports & Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "208147dc",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, StratifiedKFold, cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    roc_auc_score, roc_curve, confusion_matrix, classification_report,\n",
    "    average_precision_score, precision_recall_curve,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Visual theme ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "BG    = \"#F8F9FB\"\n",
    "STAY  = \"#4C9BE8\"\n",
    "CHURN = \"#E8604C\"\n",
    "COLORS = [\"#4C9BE8\", \"#E8A44C\", \"#5DBE7A\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\", font=\"DejaVu Sans\")\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    \"figure.facecolor\": BG, \"axes.facecolor\": BG,\n",
    "    \"axes.edgecolor\": \"#CDD3DA\", \"grid.color\": \"#E2E6EA\",\n",
    "    \"axes.titleweight\": \"bold\", \"axes.titlesize\": 13, \"font.size\": 11,\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Libraries loaded\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9ca308fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 1 · Data Cleaning & Merging\n",
    "\n",
    "The raw data is split across **two Excel sheets**:\n",
    "- `Customer_Info` — demographics (age, geography, gender, credit score, salary)\n",
    "- `Account_Info` — account activity (balance, products, churn label)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Issues found & fixed:\n",
    "| Issue | Fix |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `€` symbols in Balance & Salary | Strip `€`, cast to `float` |\n",
    "| `\"Yes\"/\"No\"` in HasCrCard & IsActiveMember | Map → `1` / `0` |\n",
    "| Typos in Geography (`FRA`, `French`) | Normalise → `France` |\n",
    "| 2 duplicate rows in Account_Info | `drop_duplicates()` |\n",
    "| 3 missing `Age` values | Drop rows (0.03% of data) |\n",
    "| `Surname` column | Drop (no predictive value) |\n",
    "| `Tenure` in both sheets | Drop from Account_Info (redundant) |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "df97a540",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Load both sheets ─────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "customer_df = pd.read_excel(\"Bank_Churn_Messy.xlsx\", sheet_name=\"Customer_Info\")\n",
    "account_df  = pd.read_excel(\"Bank_Churn_Messy.xlsx\", sheet_name=\"Account_Info\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Customer_Info : {customer_df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Account_Info  : {account_df.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3963e639",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Fix Account_Info ─────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "account_df = account_df.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "account_df = account_df.drop_duplicates(subset=\"CustomerId\", keep=\"first\")\n",
    "account_df[\"Balance\"] = account_df[\"Balance\"].str.replace(\"€\", \"\", regex=False).astype(float)\n",
    "account_df[\"IsActiveMember\"] = account_df[\"IsActiveMember\"].map({\"Yes\": 1, \"No\": 0})\n",
    "account_df[\"HasCrCard\"]      = account_df[\"HasCrCard\"].map({\"Yes\": 1, \"No\": 0})\n",
    "account_df = account_df.drop(columns=[\"Tenure\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Fix Customer_Info ─────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "customer_df = customer_df.dropna(subset=[\"Age\"])\n",
    "customer_df[\"Geography\"] = customer_df[\"Geography\"].replace({\"FRA\": \"France\", \"French\": \"France\"})\n",
    "customer_df[\"EstimatedSalary\"] = customer_df[\"EstimatedSalary\"].str.replace(\"€\", \"\", regex=False).astype(float)\n",
    "customer_df = customer_df.drop(columns=[\"Surname\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Merge & drop ID ───────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "df = pd.merge(customer_df, account_df, on=\"CustomerId\", how=\"inner\")\n",
    "df = df.drop(columns=[\"CustomerId\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFinal shape : {df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Null values :\\n{df.isnull().sum()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nChurn rate  : {df['Exited'].mean()*100:.1f}%\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
